# UIRenderSystem

## Purpose
Translates all enabled UI entities into in-frame draw events each frame. Image entities become
DrawUIQuadInFrameEvent; text entities become DrawUIStringInFrameEvent. World-space bounds are
resolved via recursive parent-chain traversal; the nesting depth is encoded as the Z component
of the transform, providing draw-layer ordering (children render over parents).

On the first frame, defers creation of RendererConfigSingletonComponent (fixed 1920x1080
orthographic camera for UI coordinate space) and returns early; rendering begins from the second
frame. Guards on EngineConfigSingletonComponent and ResourceMapSingletonComponent presence.

## Input Components
| Component | Access |
|---|---|
| EngineConfigSingletonComponent | read |
| ResourceMapSingletonComponent | read |
| RendererConfigSingletonComponent | read |
| BaseComponent | read |
| ImageComponent | read |
| TextComponent | read |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| RendererConfigSingletonComponent | add (deferred) | Created on first frame with 1920x1080 orthographic camera |
| DrawUIQuadInFrameEvent | add (inframe) | One per enabled image entity; Z encodes hierarchy depth |
| DrawUIStringInFrameEvent | add (inframe) | One per enabled text entity; Z encodes hierarchy depth |
